---
section: deploy_walkthrough
subsection: install_passenger
---
<%
@page_title = "Installing #{edition_title} + #{integration_mode_name} #{os_config_description_with_preposition} on #{infrastructure_name_with_determiner} production server (part 2) - #{deployment_walkthrough_page_title(locals)}"
content_for(:sidebar) { render_partial("_toc.html", locals: locals) }

locals[:enterprise] = edition_type == :enterprise
locals[:type] = integration_mode_type.to_s
locals[:web_server_name] = integration_mode_name

content_for(:head) do
  canonical_url = "/install/passenger_#{edition_type}_#{integration_mode_type}/#{os_config_type}/index.html"
  %Q{<link rel="canonical" href="#{url_for canonical_url}">}
end
%>

<h1>Installing <%= edition_title %> + <%= integration_mode_name %> on <%= infrastructure_name_with_determiner %> production server<br>
<small>for <%= language_name %> apps + <%= os_config_description %></small></h1>

<div class="info">
  This page describes the installation of Passenger through the following operating system configuration: <strong style="font-size: 120%"><%= os_config_description %></strong>. Not the configuration you are looking for? <a href="../install_passenger_main.html">Go back to the operating system selection menu.</a>
</div>

<% if os_config_class == :redhat %>
  <div class="warning">
    <h3 class="notoc">No Amazon Linux RPMs</h3>
    <p>
      Our YUM repository may not be used with Amazon Linux. Amazon Linux is too different from RHEL and CentOS. If you are on Amazon Linux, please  <a href="../install_passenger_main.html">go back to the operating system selection menu</a> and select "Other" as operating system.
    </p>
  </div>
<% end %>

<p class="lead">On this page, we will install Passenger. After installing Passenger we can begin with deploying the app.</p>

<div>
  <p><strong>Table of contents</strong></p>
  <ul class="toc-container"><li>Loading...</li></ul>
</div>

<%= render_partial("/install/install/shared/#{os_config_class}.html",
      locals: locals.merge(menu_selection_url: "../install_passenger_main.html")) %>

<h2>Next step</h2>
<p>
  Now that you have installed Passenger, you are ready to deploy your <%= language_name %> application on the production server!
</p>

<p>
  <a href="deploy_app.html" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Continue: Deploy app &raquo;</a>
</p>
